.TH "thom" "1" "2026-06-10" "" "thom User Manuals"
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
thom - Thomson TO7-70 home computer emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]thom\f[R] [\f[B]-m\f[R] \f[I]file.m7\f[R]] [\f[B]-nodisk\f[R]]
[\f[B]-fast\f[R]] [\f[B]-nosound\f[R]] [\f[B]-geometry\f[R]
\f[I]wxh+x+y\f[R]] [\f[B]-noshm\f[R]] [\f[B]-display\f[R]
\f[I]displayname\f[R]] [\f[B]-help\f[R]]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
\f[B]thom\f[R] emulates the Thomson TO7-70, a French 8-bit home computer
based on the Motorola MC6809E processor.
It faithfully reproduces the hardware of the TO7-70, including the
MC6809E CPU, memory card, video card, and the following peripherals:
optical pen (light pen), joysticks, cassette tape reader, and floppy
disk controller.
.PP
The emulator requires an X11 display and GTK+ 1.2.
Sound output is provided via PulseAudio.
.PP
The TO7-70 ROM is not included for copyright reasons and must be
obtained separately.
ROM files must be placed in \f[B]/usr/share/thom/\f[R].
.SS Control Panel
.PP
Pressing \f[B]ESC\f[R] suspends emulation and opens the control panel.
From this menu, the following operations are available:
.IP \[bu] 2
Reset the TO7-70 (equivalent to pressing the Reset button on the
machine)
.IP \[bu] 2
Cold restart (power cycle)
.IP \[bu] 2
Adjust emulation speed: exact (MC6809E at 1 MHz) or maximum (full speed,
disables sound)
.IP \[bu] 2
Manage the cartridge slot (Mémo7 format, \f[I].m7\f[R])
.IP \[bu] 2
Manage the cassette tape reader (\f[I].k7\f[R] format)
.IP \[bu] 2
Manage up to four floppy disk drives (\f[I].sap\f[R] format, Thomson
5\[rq]25 360 KB)
.SS Keyboard
.PP
The TO7-70 keyboard is fully emulated on an AZERTY layout.
Key mappings:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]STOP\f[R] → Tab
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]CNT\f[R] → Left Ctrl
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]RAZ\f[R] → End
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]ACC\f[R] → Alt
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]HOME\f[R] → Home
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]INS\f[R] → Insert
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]EFF\f[R] → Delete
.IP \[bu] 2
Arrow keys → Arrow keys
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[B]#\f[R] is mapped to \f[B]ù\f[R] (Shift+2)
.SS Joysticks
.PP
The numeric keypad emulates joystick 0 (8 directions); Fire is mapped to
Right Ctrl.
The left keyboard block (A\[en]E, Q\[en]D, W\[en]C) emulates joystick 1
while still sending the corresponding letters to the TO7-70; Fire is
mapped to Left Ctrl.
.SS Optical Pen
.PP
The mouse emulates the TO7-70 optical pen.
The left button acts as the pen tip.
The right button toggles the mouse cursor visibility.
.SS Sound
.PP
Both the internal 1-bit sound generator and the external 6-bit generator
(Musique et Jeux interface) are emulated.
Sound is output via PulseAudio.
.SS Graphics Modes
.PP
The emulator supports 8, 16, 24, and 32-bit X11 color depths.
The default window size is 640x400; the \f[B]-geometry 320x200\f[R]
option selects a smaller, faster-rendering window.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\f[B]-help\f[R]
Display command-line help.
.TP
\f[B]-m\f[R] \f[I]file.m7\f[R]
Load the Mémo7 ROM cartridge image \f[I]file.m7\f[R] at startup.
.TP
\f[B]-nodisk\f[R]
Disable the floppy disk controller.
.TP
\f[B]-fast\f[R]
Start the emulator at maximum speed (sound is disabled in this mode).
.TP
\f[B]-nosound\f[R]
Disable sound output.
.TP
\f[B]-geometry\f[R] \f[I]wxh+x+y\f[R]
Set the window geometry.
Two sizes are supported: \f[B]640x400\f[R] (default) and
\f[B]320x200\f[R] (faster rendering).
.TP
\f[B]-noshm\f[R]
Disable the MIT-SHM X11 shared memory extension.
.TP
\f[B]-display\f[R] \f[I]displayname\f[R]
Specify the X server to connect to.
.SH FILES
.TP
\f[I]/usr/share/thom/\f[R]
Directory where the TO7-70 ROM files must be placed.
.TP
\f[I]memo7/\f[R]
Recommended directory for Mémo7 ROM cartridge images (\f[I].m7\f[R]).
.TP
\f[I]k7/\f[R]
Recommended directory for cassette tape images (\f[I].k7\f[R]).
.TP
\f[I]disks/\f[R]
Recommended directory for Thomson 5\[rq]25 floppy disk images
(\f[I].sap\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the emulator with default settings:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
thom
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Start the emulator with a Mémo7 cartridge preloaded:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
thom -m memo7/basic128.m7
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Start at maximum speed (no sound):
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
thom -fast -nosound
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Start in 320x200 windowed mode:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
thom -geometry 320x200
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
Connect to a specific X server:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
thom -display :1
\f[R]
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.PP
\f[B]xrandr\f[R](1)
.SH BUGS
.PP
No known bugs.
